<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-51-1021 </DOCNO><TEXT>With this book, a documentation is presented of the various argumentsput forward in the Augsburg court proceedings on forest decline and itscauses, namely by an expert opinion that states the reasons for takinglegal action on the part of Augsburg municipality, and a statement dealingwith the 'effective legal protection of property in forest'. The expertopinion analyses the legal situation in search for further reasons extendingthe legal basis of the claims beyond the points given in the expert opinionof Leisner in 1983. The points referred to are: claims for compensationunder section 14, second sentence of the BImSchG (Act on Protection AgainstEnvironmental Hazards and Pollution); public liability claims under theBImSchG; claims created by interference with property that is equal toexpropriation; criticism of the protective doctrine in the field of fundamentalrights. (HSCH).</TEXT></DOC>